Class NodeStylePortStyleAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles.NodeStylePortStyleAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPortStyle, ICloneable, Cloneable

    public class NodeStylePortStyleAdapter
extends Object
implements IPortStyle, Cloneable
    A port style decorator that uses a node style instance to render the port.

    • Constructor Detail

      • NodeStylePortStyleAdapter

        public NodeStylePortStyleAdapter()
        Initializes a new instance of the NodeStylePortStyleAdapter class.

        This constructor uses an ellipse ShapeNodeStyle with a black brush for the NodeStyle property.

      • NodeStylePortStyleAdapter

        public NodeStylePortStyleAdapter(INodeStyle nodeStyle)
        Creates a port style that uses the provided node style to render the port.

        Note that the styles will be stored by reference, thus modifying the style will directly affect the rendering of this instance.

        Parameters:
        nodeStyle - The style to use for rendering the port.
